V = π(5)²(13.5) = 78.5π cubic meters.

The height of the cone is h/2 = 13.5/2 = 6.75 meters. Since the radius of the cone is also r = 5 meters, we can use the formula for the volume of a cone: V = (1/3)πr²h. Substituting the values, we get:

V = (1/3)π(5)²(6.75) ≈ 23.25π cubic meters.

The total volume of the silo is the sum of the volumes of the cylinder and the cone. Therefore,

Total volume = V_cylinder + V_cone = 78.5π + 23.25π = 101.75π cubic meters.

